<div class="postcell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
                
<p>I was wondering if there was a better way to capture a value inside an input tag rather than using regex in JS.</p>
<pre class="default s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-swift"><span class="hljs-string">"&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body onload=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>document.form1.submit()<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>&gt;&lt;form name=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>form1<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> method=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>post<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> action=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span><span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> &gt;&lt;input name=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>Token<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> type=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>hidden<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> value=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span><span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>&gt;&lt;input name=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>ID<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> type=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>hidden<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> value=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>12120012732dafd4<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>&gt;&lt;/form&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"</span>
</code></pre>
<p>Ideally I would like to capture just the ID value <code>12120012732dafd4</code></p>
    </div>

