<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>Since there is no DOM in node you have to initialize a cheerio instance from an HTML string. (this example comes from the cheerio readme)</p>
<pre class="default s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-swift"> <span class="hljs-keyword">var</span> cheerio <span class="hljs-operator">=</span> require('cheerio'),
        $ <span class="hljs-operator">=</span> cheerio.load(<span class="hljs-string">"&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body onload=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>document.form1.submit()<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>&gt;&lt;form name=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>form1<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> method=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>post<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> action=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span><span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> &gt;&lt;input name=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>Token<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> type=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>hidden<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> value=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span><span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>&gt;&lt;input name=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>ID<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> type=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>hidden<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span> value=<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>12120012732dafd4<span class="hljs-subst">\"</span>&gt;&lt;/form&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;"</span>
);
    
    $('input').val();
</code></pre>
    </div>
